Show Description

From the Infowars web site :: On this Monday, November 25 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Alex breaks down new developments in bankster schemes and surveillance tech which showcase the establishment's tightening grip on the American people. 

We now have an exclusive photo of a helicopter drone which can be used for domestic surveillance. Developed by Northrop Grumman, the drone is small enough to be towed on a flatbed trailer behind a pick-up truck. 

In other news, banks are threatening to start charging consumers fees for depositing money into their bank accounts. 

Dan Bongino, an author and a former member of the Secret Service's Presidential Protection Division, joins the show to reveal the inner workings of the Obama administration and the catalyst which caused him to leave his 12-year career with the Secret Service.

NOTE: This is the PrisonPlanet members' edit, from which scheduled commercial breaks have been removed. It is the whole broadcast in one MP3.
